<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-08-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-08-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="733" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d733">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">871.51/251</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Roumanian Legation</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <p rend="center"><hi rend="smallcaps">Memorandum</hi></p>
                        <p>It has come to the knowledge of the Roumanian Government that some of the
                            gold that reaches the United States at present, is part of the Roumanian
                            gold which was sent in 1916 to Moscow for safety, and is used by the
                            Soviet Authorities to make payments abroad.</p>
                        <p>The Roumanian Government … considers himself obliged to formulate
                            reservations as to its final distribution.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <dateline rendition="#left">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                                </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-08-15"><hi rend="italic">August 15, 1921</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>